  "title": "PLC & Commissioning Engineer (West) - Up to $4200",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Develop green marine solutions that reduces marine carbon footprint, in line with company business objectives.</p><p>· Hands on in setting up of test lab to enable development and testing.</p><p>· Perform PLC software and algorithm development for electrical propulsion solutions.</p><p>· Generate documentation of software architecture and logic flow, test procedures, quality control and any other necessary supporting documents.</p><p>· Participate and support commissioning of vessels with similar configurations.</p><p>· Troubleshoot and resolve any issues related to our delivered solutions that may arise during the vessel commissioning.</p><p>· Any other tasks as may be required by supervisor.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Min engineering degree in relevant discipline</p><p>· Strong software development skills particularly in equipment controls</p><p>· Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>· Hands on person</p><p>· Team player</p><p>· Good communicator and has no problem engaging with external parties</p><p>· Knowledge in power electronics, motor drives, marine propulsion systems is a plus<br /><br /><br /><strong>Interested and suitable candidate kindly click quick apply. Resume will be forwarded to Stepfan Soon Yit</strong></p><p><strong>We regret that only suitable candidate will be notified.</strong></p><p><strong>GEMS Recruit/EA License : 23C1459</strong></p><p><strong>EA Personnel No : R24120893 (Stepfan Soon Yit)</strong></p>",
